name: Office Space for Rent in Tambo, Parañaque at PITX Office Tower 3 | 8F, 3180.37 sqm
description: About PITX Office Towers PITX (Parañaque Integrated Terminal Exchange) is a transportation hub serving 100,000 passengers daily. While primarily known for its efficient transportation services, PITX also offers a range of amenities and facilities, including four towers for office space areas. These office spaces within PITX provide a modern and convenient workplace hub for businesses, entrepreneurs, and professionals.  PITX Office Towers Features and Amenities The office towers at PITX offer flexible workspaces catering to the diverse needs of businesses. From small to large enterprises, these towers provide a range of office spaces, including private offices, open-plan work areas, meeting rooms, and collaborative spaces. The flexible leasing options enable businesses to scale up or down as per their requirements, making it an ideal choice for startups and growing companies. PITX Office Towers offer:  Dormitory Affordable employee cafeteria Supermarket, F&B, and Retail Options Highly secured building based on OST guidelines Transportation and Connectivity through Bus, Grab/Taxi, Jeepney and Soon LRT 100% Back-Up Power 24/7 Accessible   Situate your business at PITX for better accessibility and easier commutes for clients and employees. PITX offers custom-fit options, adjustable according to your desired concept. PITX Office Towers also offer flexible lease terms, creating a collaborative relationship between the lessee and lessor.  Average Rental Rate of Office Spaces for Rent in PITX Office Towers PITX Office Towers provide value-for-money office spaces perfect for all types of businesses. Available for rent in PITX Office Towers are custom-fit office spaces with an average rate of PhP 90,000 to PhP 2.2 million. Take note that the rate varies depending on the floor area and inclusions.  Financing Options You can explore financing options for PITX Office Towers for rent with commercial loans. You can apply for commercial loans from banks. The principal loan amount varies depending on factors like credit score.  Why PITX Office Towers is the Perfect Commercial Option for You The office towers are nestled within the terminal, which offers access for your employees to an easier commuting experience daily. Aside from the transportation options, there are Food and Beverage, Retail, and Grocery options within the terminal. This accessibility enhances connectivity and convenience for businesses operating from these towers.  About Parañaque A premier city, Parañaque is located in the southern region of Metro Manila. It is a fringe city because it is located in Metro Manila's periphery. It provides the same advantages as other cities in Metro Manila but at a reduced price because it is a periphery city. Las Piñas, Muntinlupa, Manila Bay, Taguig, and Pasay all border Parañaque to the southeast, southwest, west, and north, respectively. A variety of corporate offices, opulent hotels, and entertainment venues can be found in mixed-use buildings in Parañaque. This presents various prospects for real estate buyers and investors. For people looking to start a business, Parañaque is the perfect place.  Address: #1 Kennedy Rd., Brgy. Tambo, Parañaque City 1701, Metro Manila Year Built: 2018 Turnover Date: May 2023 Total No. of Buildings: 4 Total No. of Units: 28

description: Code : DS882597/DR881467 Category : For Rent Project : Commercial Lot City : Marina Bay City, Tambo, Paranaque City Unit : Commercial Lot Size : 2,800 sqmRental Price : Php 2,800,000.00 NET Details of the Property: • Clean Title • Facing East and West  Nearby Landmarks: • Okada Manila • Resorts World • Solaire • Marina Bay Homes (Residential)  Barangay Tambo is primarily a residential, then a commercial community. Most of the commercial establishments and manufacturing companies are located along Quirino Avenue, MIA Rd, Roxas Blvd., Macapagal Avenue and Aseana City where soon to rise Entertainment City. These include Uniwide Coastal Mall, Pearl Plaza, Sony Warehouse, and Asia Brewery warehouse. There are also various restaurants, brokerages, commercial banks, gasoline stations, clinic and burger stands. This once grassy place has turned out to be a center of progress, maybe because of its proximity to such important hubs as Metro Manila’s airports. Almost all business establishments are eyeing Tambo as one prime location where business can be really visible.  Why Buying a Property in the South of Metro Manila 1. It Is a Rapidly Developing Urban Hub It has its own central business district, shopping malls for both high end and mid-market, international schools, top-notch hospitals, and its own convenient access to the rest of southern Luzon  2. It Is Near the Manila Airport living in the south will cost less time to get to the airport than when traveling from the north. Since terminals of the Ninoy Aquino International Airports are just a short drive away from Muntinlupa, Parañaque, and Las Piñas  3. The Area Is Mostly Flood-free Based on the findings of the Department of Environment and Natural Resources’ Mines and Geosciences Bureau, most of the flood-free to least flooded cities can be found in the south of Metro Manila. This can be attributed to the cities’ land slopes, effective drainage cleaning and maintenance, garbage and waste management, mandatory use of eco-friendly materials, implementation of carbon footprint deduction ways, and the area’s lush greeneries that help reduce risk of flooding  If you’re interested in RENTING this property or wish to SELL a property, don't hesitate to contact us: Bien Singson Licensed Real Estate Broker PRC#0005179

description: Code : DS882597/DR881467 Category : For Rent Project : Commercial Lot City : Marina Bay City, Tambo, Paranaque City Unit : Commercial Lot Size : 2,800 sqmRental Price : Php 2,800,000.00 NET Details of the Property: • Clean Title • Facing East and West  Nearby Landmarks: • Okada Manila • Resorts World • Solaire • Marina Bay Homes (Residential)  Barangay Tambo is primarily a residential, then a commercial community. Most of the commercial establishments and manufacturing companies are located along Quirino Avenue, MIA Rd, Roxas Blvd., Macapagal Avenue and Aseana City where soon to rise Entertainment City. These include Uniwide Coastal Mall, Pearl Plaza, Sony Warehouse, and Asia Brewery warehouse. There are also various restaurants, brokerages, commercial banks, gasoline stations, clinic and burger stands. This once grassy place has turned out to be a center of progress, maybe because of its proximity to such important hubs as Metro Manila’s airports. Almost all business establishments are eyeing Tambo as one prime location where business can be really visible.  Why Buying a Property in the South of Metro Manila 1. It Is a Rapidly Developing Urban Hub It has its own central business district, shopping malls for both high end and mid-market, international schools, top-notch hospitals, and its own convenient access to the rest of southern Luzon  2. It Is Near the Manila Airport living in the south will cost less time to get to the airport than when traveling from the north. Since terminals of the Ninoy Aquino International Airports are just a short drive away from Muntinlupa, Parañaque, and Las Piñas  3. The Area Is Mostly Flood-free Based on the findings of the Department of Environment and Natural Resources’ Mines and Geosciences Bureau, most of the flood-free to least flooded cities can be found in the south of Metro Manila. This can be attributed to the cities’ land slopes, effective drainage cleaning and maintenance, garbage and waste management, mandatory use of eco-friendly materials, implementation of carbon footprint deduction ways, and the area’s lush greeneries that help reduce risk of flooding  If you’re interested in RENTING this property or wish to SELL a property, don't hesitate to contact us: Bien Singson Licensed Real Estate Broker PRC#0005179

name: House/Compound For Rent in Tambo, Parañaque City, Metro Manila
description:
Two residential homes situated in a compound within a compound. It used to be an exclusive family compound occupied by the old respected families of Paranaque. These compounds used to be the homes also of the consulates of US Embassy and some prominent families like former President Marcos, vice -president and senators of the Philippines. Side by side, it used to be the residence of the owners of prominent and respected business tycoons such as Meralco and Philcomsat. It’s location is almost a stone’s throw-away from the International and Domestic Airports, at Barangay Tambo Paranaque City. It is in the heart of the Entertaiment City, where big hotels, casinos and malls like Solare Hotel, City or Dreams, Novo Hotel, Hyatt Hotel, Crown Hotel, and Microtel are located. Aside from the hotels, it is almost a kilometer away from Ayala Mall and Mall of Asia. Apart from these malls and hotels, it is also 5 minutes away from Baclaran church and its commercial surrounding, the haven of bargain hunters. Two Public markets are also in the vicinity. Transportation wise, it is also a stone’s throw-away from PITX, Paranaque Integrated Terminal Exchange, which is the bus terminal connecting metro manila to all provinces. It is also accessible to other forms of transportations such as jeepneys and trycicles. It is close to the several skyway entrances to ramps and CAVITEX (Cavite express way).

Parañaque, officially the City of Parañaque, is a 1st class highly urbanized city in the National Capital Region of the Philippines. According to the 2020 census, it has a population of 689,992 people.

Parañaque is the home of the PAGCOR Entertainment City, a gaming and entertainment complex under development by the state owned Philippine Amusement and Gaming Corporation spanning an area of 8 km2 (3.1 sq mi) in Bay City, where four large integrated resorts are based namely Solaire Resort & Casino, City of Dreams Manila, Okada Manila, and the soon to be completed Westside City Resorts World. It is also the home of the Parañaque Integrated Terminal Exchange public transport and the Aseana City business district development which includes Ayala Malls Manila Bay.

Sentosia: A Condominium Development in Don Galo, Parañaque by Manila Prime Land Holdings, Inc.

Sentosia Condominium is a residential development by Manila Prime Land Holdings, Inc. in Don Galo, Parañaque. This 1.7-hectare complex comprises 127 duplex and quadruplex condos with three bedrooms, two bathrooms, three bedrooms, and a garage. Apart from units, this development also has various amenities.

Why is Sentosia the Perfect Condominium Option in Don Galo, Parañaque?

Sentosia in Don Galo, Parañaque, is perfect for people who want to be near the city's upscale malls, casinos, and restaurants. It's a short drive from the SM Mall of Asia, one of the most popular shopping destinations in the country.

The City of Dreams, a prestigious hotel and casino complex, is only a short walk away, too. Frequent flyers will feel right at home in this condo complex, as it's only 15 minutes away from Ninoy Aquino International Airport (NAIA).

Secure facilities - Guards monitor the entrance and exit gates 24/7 to ensure that only residents and authorized visitors can access the condo complex. The development also has high perimeter fences which deter trespassing.

Updated utilities - Sentosia has an uninterruptible water supply and internet and cable television provisions.

Recreational amenities - Residents can hold events in the clubhouse. 

There's also a swimming pool and meditation garden where people can relax after a hard day's work. This condominium development also has a gym, perfect for residents or tenants who want to stay active.

description: About PITX Office Towers PITX (Parañaque Integrated Terminal Exchange) is a transportation hub serving 100,000 passengers daily. While primarily known for its efficient transportation services, PITX also offers a range of amenities and facilities, including four towers for office space areas. These office spaces within PITX provide a modern and convenient workplace hub for businesses, entrepreneurs, and professionals.  PITX Office Towers Features and Amenities The office towers at PITX offer flexible workspaces catering to the diverse needs of businesses. From small to large enterprises, these towers provide a range of office spaces, including private offices, open-plan work areas, meeting rooms, and collaborative spaces. The flexible leasing options enable businesses to scale up or down as per their requirements, making it an ideal choice for startups and growing companies. PITX Office Towers offer:  Dormitory Affordable employee cafeteria Supermarket, F&B, and Retail Options Highly secured building based on OST guidelines Transportation and Connectivity through Bus, Grab/Taxi, Jeepney and Soon LRT 100% Back-Up Power 24/7 Accessible   Situate your business at PITX for better accessibility and easier commutes for clients and employees. PITX offers custom-fit options, adjustable according to your desired concept. PITX Office Towers also offer flexible lease terms, creating a collaborative relationship between the lessee and lessor.  Average Rental Rate of Office Spaces for Rent in PITX Office Towers PITX Office Towers provide value-for-money office spaces perfect for all types of businesses. Available for rent in PITX Office Towers are custom-fit office spaces with an average rate of PhP 90,000 to PhP 2.2 million.
